-- India's Monsoonal Rainfall Seen Increasing Over Eastern, Central Areas
-- Pratik Parija
-- 2010-07-17T08:37:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/india-s-monsoonal-rainfall-seen-increasing-over-eastern-central-areas.html

          
          
             India’s monsoon rainfall may
increase over eastern, central and southern parts of the country
between July 24 and July 30, the nation’s meteorological
department said on its website yesterday.  
 Rain may be widespread in western parts of Madhya Pradesh,
some parts of Maharashtra and Gujarat by July 18, the weather
office said. Rains may be widespread in the west coast and
eastern parts of Uttar Pradesh between July 17 and July 23, it
said.  
 Madhya Pradesh is India’s biggest soybean grower, while
Uttar Pradesh and Maharashtra are the nation’s largest sugar
cane producers. Gujarat is the country’s biggest peanut
producer.  
